        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 3:21PM EDT by NWS Morristown TN</headline>
        <description>At 321 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Madisonville, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sweetwater, Madisonville, Vonore, Greenback, Philadelphia, Fort
Loudon State Park, McGee Carson Peninsula, and Tellico Village.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
